				\usepackage{amsbsy}
				\usepackage{mathrsfs}
				\usepackage{upgreek}
				\setlength{\oddsidemargin}{-69pt}
				\begin{document}$$\upmu$$\end{document}m in diameter than conventional gas atomization.268 An interesting application of plasma torches is the production of sustainable turquoise hydrogen and carbon for use in the metallurgical industry. The electricity consumption of plasma torches is however a potential obstacle.269

